Known debt:
  ‚úò Unbounded channels / no backpressure - (`crates/core/src/plugin.rs:125`). A system that emits faster than JS drains grows the queue without bound. Bound them or document. @cancelled(26-07-01 13:05)
  ‚úî Proper error handling e.g. incorrect prop/style values - no malformed style prop can throw from `op_flush` any more (a throw there aborted the whole commit batch and wedged the reconciler mid-commit ‚Üí frozen UI). Bad unit-bearing values (`Length`/`Angle`/`Time`/`FontSize`), `Rect` shorthand tokens / value-counts (`padding`/`margin`/`border`/`borderRadius`), and unknown rect/`borderColor` side keys now all warn + fall back to a default instead of erroring (`protocol` uses the neutral `tracing` facade, staying bevy-type-free). The silent enum mappers (`display`/`align*`/`justify*`/`flexDirection`/‚Ä¶ via `unknown_keyword`), grid track parsing, and `fontWeight` now warn on unrecognized values too, matching the existing color/`fontFamily` warn+fallback pattern. NOTE remaining gap: a wrong JSON *type* for a scalar field (`width={{}}`/`width={true}`) still throws from `deserialize_any`; TS guards it (`js/src/jsx.d.ts`), so deferred. Also hardened the hot-reload path (`js_thread.rs`): a rebuilt bundle that throws on execution ‚Äî a syntax error OR a runtime error like `padding: aa16` (undefined identifier) ‚Äî is now REJECTED rather than applied; the loop re-runs the last working bundle (re-parking the event loop) instead of escalating to a destructive full rebuild and then `break`ing the JS thread (which used to freeze the UI permanently with no recovery). Covered by `crates/core/tests/broken_reload.rs`. Remaining: a broken *initial* (cold-start) bundle still can't start (no last-good to fall back to). @done(26-06-30 16:44)
  ‚òë Panic audit on JS-derived data - audited: no production hot path uses `.expect()`/bare `.unwrap()` on JS-derived data (all use `.unwrap_or*`). The flagged `.expect()`s are all test-only: `crates/core/src/anchor.rs:214`/`:217` are inside `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` (`props_deserialize_anchor`), and the old `reconcile.rs:674 .expect("valid text props")` is now `reconcile.rs:1523` in a test helper. (The request path already rejects on bad input; serde-boundary failures no longer panic ‚Äî see "Proper error handling" above.)
  ‚úî Full `Node` rebuild on every `Op::Update` - `apply_style` (`crates/core/src/ui_map.rs`) now updates `Node` in place via a queued `EntityCommand` (`set_node_if_changed`) that `set_if_neq`s the freshly-built node, so a paint-only change (e.g. `backgroundColor`) no longer marks `Node` changed and no longer forces a `bevy_ui` relayout of the subtree. Centralized at the single funnel, so `Op::Update` AND the hover/press restyle systems (`apply_interaction_styles`/`apply_surface_interaction_styles`) all benefit. Measured via the stress `updateEvery2ndBackgroundColor` op (relayout gone) vs `updateEvery2ndText` (relayout retained, as it must). Remaining: the hand-maintained `Style`‚Üí`Node` mirror list (`node_from_style`) still must match `Node` field-for-field ‚Äî easy to desync, but that's a maintenance concern, not perf. @done(26-07-01)
  ‚úî Descendant leak on single-node removal - (`crates/core/src/reconcile.rs:230`). @done(26-07-01 14:36)
  ‚úî Surface JS runtime errors - the prelude now installs a `console` that forwards every `console.*` call (and the runtime's own error handlers) to the Bevy log via `op_log`, tagged `target: "js"` with the tracing level distinguishing `log`/`warn`/`error`. @done(26-06-30 16:44)
  ‚úò Single-root / single-isolate - limitation (`crates/core/src/plugin.rs:312`) ‚Äî one UI surface per app. Document explicitly. @cancelled(26-07-01 14:41)

Features:
  ‚úî `<editableText>` completeness (IME, clipboard, selection) + accessibility. IME and clipboard (Ctrl+C/V/X) already worked via Bevy's `EditableTextInputPlugin`; bridged the rest to React: `onSelect` + controlled `selectionStart`/`selectionEnd` (UTF-8 byte offsets via parley's `select_byte_range`), `onFocus`/`onBlur` + `autofocus`, a `composing` flag on change/select, and an `AccessibilityNode` (`TextInput`/`MultilineTextInput`) with `ariaLabel` + live value sync. Deferred: `placeholder` (overlay text entity), `readOnly` (edit-blocking), full accesskit text-selection (needs parley's run subtree). @done(26-06-27)
  ‚úî named colors - CSS named colors (basic + extended palettes) + `transparent`, via the shared `bevy_react_canvas::parse_css_color`. @done(26-06-25)
  ‚úî proper units support in styles - colors gained named/`rgb()`/`hsl()`/`hwb()`/`oklab()`/`oklch()` notation (warn+magenta on a typo, no longer silent white); new `Angle` (deg/rad/turn/grad, bare number = degrees ‚Äî `transform.rotate` now degrees, was radians) and `Time` (ms/s, bare number = ms, ms‚Üís conversion moved from JS into Rust) wire types decode at the serde boundary like `Length`; `lineHeight`/`letterSpacing` accept CSS unit strings. Lengths were already a complete `Val` mirror. NOTE: `Length`/`Angle`/`Time` no longer fail-fast on a bad string ‚Äî handled under "Proper error handling" above (they warn + fall back to default at the serde boundary via the `tracing` facade). @done(26-06-25)
