        ‚úî `FocusPolicy` (Block/Pass) - `focusPolicy` style prop maps to `bevy::ui::FocusPolicy` (`"block"`‚Üí`Block`, `"pass"`‚Üí`Pass`); `apply_style` always inserts (never removes ‚Äî removal would silently fall back to `Block`). Element-dependent default: a `<button>` blocks (captures the click, mirroring bevy_ui's native `Button`; re-asserted in the reconciler's create + update paths via `apply_button_focus_default`), a `<node>`/container passes ‚Äî so a `<text>` or wrapper never swallows clicks meant for what's behind/around it. Also fixed: `onClick` now attaches an `Interaction` so a bare `<node onClick>` (no hover/press/pointer prop) is actually clickable. Demo: Styling ‚Üí "Focus Policy" toggles a front box between pass/block over a clickable back box. @done(26-06-29)
        ‚úî Controlled `ScrollPosition` - scroll input is handled (`scroll.rs`), but offset can't be set/read from React. @done(26-06-29 14:01)
